263. The meaning is that after a defeat none of his opponents are innocent in the eonqueror's eyes and he is then sole judge (bem mutato iudice). ,

264 sq. ‘It is not my fortunes that are at stake3 it is you that 1 implore to be free men, to be sovran over the world.' The thought and the emphasis are both highly artificial. For a similar ‘ prayer ’ see 68 sqq. supra.
